1. File & Directory Management

pwd – Show current working directory

ls – List files and directories

ls -l → long format

ls -a → show hidden files

cd – Change directory

mkdir – Create a directory

touch – Create empty file or update timestamp

cp – Copy files or directories

cp -r → recursive copy for directories

mv – Move or rename files

rm – Remove files

rm -r → remove directory recursively

find – Search for files

find /path -name "*.log"

2. File Viewing & Editing

cat – View file content

less – Scroll through file content

head / tail – View first or last lines of a file

tail -f file.log → live log monitoring

nano / vi / vim – Edit files in terminal

3. File Permissions & Ownership
chmod – Change file permissions

chmod 755 file.sh

chown – Change ownership

chown user:group file

umask – Default permission settings

4. Process & Service Management
ps – List running processes

ps aux → all processes

top / htop – Monitor processes in real-time

kill – Kill process by PID

kill -9 PID → force kill

systemctl – Manage services

systemctl status nginx

systemctl restart docker

service – Older way to manage services

5. Networking Commands
ifconfig / ip addr – Show IP configuration

ping – Test network connectivity

curl – Send HTTP requests

wget – Download files from URLs

netstat -tulnp – Show listening ports (deprecated; use ss)

ss -tulnp – Show socket statistics

telnet – Test connectivity to a port

nslookup / dig – DNS lookup

6. Disk Management
df -h – Show disk usage (human-readable)

du -sh folder/ – Show folder size

mount / umount – Mount or unmount file systems

lsblk – List block devices

7. User & Group Management
whoami – Show current user

who – Show logged-in users

id – Show UID, GID, groups

adduser / useradd – Create user

passwd – Change password

usermod – Modify user

groupadd – Add new group

8. Archiving & Compression
tar -cvf file.tar folder/ – Create tar archive

tar -xvf file.tar – Extract tar archive

gzip file / gunzip file.gz – Compress/decompress

zip -r file.zip folder/ – Create zip

unzip file.zip – Extract zip

9. Log & Monitoring Commands
journalctl – View system logs

dmesg – Kernel messages

tail -f /var/log/syslog – Follow logs

10. Package Management
Debian/Ubuntu:

apt update – Update package index

apt install package – Install

apt remove package – Uninstall

RHEL/CentOS:

yum install package

yum remove package

Fedora:

dnf install package

11. SSH & Remote Access
ssh user@host – Connect to remote server

scp file user@host:/path – Secure copy

rsync -av source/ user@host:/path – Sync files

12. Scripting & Automation
bash script.sh – Run shell script

crontab -e – Schedule jobs

env – Show environment variables

export VAR=value – Set environment variable

